Ginny and Me: Reflections of What God Can Do

Brief Autobiography that Packs a Punch Full of Hope, Light and God's Grace

When I learned that Christine was a published writer, I immediately purchased the book from Amazon in an effort to support her endeavors. I'm a lover of great books with solid life lessons and don't give out rave reviews lightly. When I received the book and noted that it is less than 100 pages, I figured I would have an easy read, learn more about my colleague and be happy that I could invest in her pursuit. I'm not sure that I expected read Ginny and Me and have my faith strengthened immensely as I go through my own trials in life. Within the first few pages, you will learn that Christine has been through so very much in her years on earth, but consistently through this book you see her spirit of gratitude to God, her forgiveness of those who wronged her, and her solid belief that God hears and answers our prayers. I have not had many of the harrowing experiences as this author, but I still walked away from this book with lessons on perseverance/faith, affirmations of goodness in the land of the living and confirmations that God is ALWAYS for his children. If you are struggling with anything in your life and just need example after example that no matter how hurtful/hard life can be sometimes, you have an Advocate and Helper on your side, buy this book. While simply telling her story and not trying to paint either a pretty or grim picture of her life, Christine packs testimony after testimony of God keeping her in His hands and always working things out for good whether it be mental illness, abuse, homelessness, potential death from pregnancy, violence, depression or (believe it or not) much more. If He does it for one, He is able and willing to do it for all.
